The researchers used DNA testing to identify the geographic origin of 6.5 tons of contraband ivory seized in Singapore in June 2002.
A team of US scientists has used DNA testing to identify the geographic origin of poached elephant tusks--research they hope may help curb the illegal ivory trade.
Resurgence of illicit trade in African elephant ivory is placing the elephant at renewed risk," the scientists said in a study published this week in the Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences.
